# Orchestrator — Maryland Driveway Restore

## Slug
`maryland-driveway-restore` (run dir + demo dir + /work-samples route all use this)

## Startup brief (one-paragraph)
Premium driveway-restoration company in Maryland needs a Phase 1 marketing site
launched in ~1 week, fixed-price ~$850–$1,200, hosted on Rocket.net, built in
WordPress + Bricks + Rank Math + Fluent Forms + Site Kit. Mobile-first, luxury
aesthetic (Apple / Restoration Hardware / luxury home-builder), deep charcoal +
white + forest green, big before/after photography, sticky "Call Now" + "Text a
Photo" CTAs. Core deliverable is lead generation (phone calls + text estimate
requests) plus local-SEO foundation (GA4, Search Console, GBP, schema). Phase 2
(separately quoted): 30–50 city/neighborhood landing pages, learning center,
video library, interactive estimate calculator, case studies, advanced local
SEO — framed as an ongoing multi-state relationship. Michael's note: wants a REAL
WordPress demo on his backend at the michaelwegter.com domain, and wants to cite
his SEO + Google Analytics work on **fortherecordmn.com** as proof.

## Central architecture decision (FLAG for planner + CEO) — read carefully
Michael's request (Docker WordPress + a dedicated Cloudflare tunnel subdomain) is
in DIRECT tension with this repo's hard rule: `~/.cloudflared/config.yml` is
sacred, routes 100% of traffic to Flask :5050, and `run-server.ps1` self-heals
any separate ingress within ~10s. **A standalone `client-demo.yourdomain.com`
tunnel route is NOT allowed and will be auto-killed.** Do NOT pursue Option 3 as
written.

Reconciled options, in priority order:

1. **(Recommended default) Bespoke static premium demo** in
   `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/maryland-driveway-restore/`, served at
   `michaelwegter.com/demos/maryland-driveway-restore/` and iframed by
   `/work-samples/maryland-driveway-restore`. This is the workflow's proven
   same-origin model: zero deploy friction, no tunnel risk, fully functional
   (working estimate form, sticky CTAs, before/after sliders, FAQ schema, all 8
   Phase-1 pages). It reproduces the WordPress *experience and design* faithfully
   without needing WP itself. Lead-gen form posts to a small Flask blueprint
   (mw-backend) so "Text a Photo / Free Estimate" actually captures and persists.
   At feature richness 10: build all 8 pages + the dedicated `/free-estimate` QR
   landing page, real before/after slider component, working multi-step estimate
   form with photo upload, embedded schema (LocalBusiness/Service/FAQ/Review),
   GA4-ready event hooks, and a service-area map. This is the safe, high-polish
   path that satisfies every hard gate.

2. **(Stretch, only if greenlit by CEO and time/budget allow) Real WordPress
   container on the Surface, bridged through Flask** — NOT through a separate
   tunnel. Run WP+MySQL in Docker on a loopback port, register it as a service in
   `services.json`, and expose it via a Flask **bridge blueprint**
   (`bridge_blueprint_template.py`, PREFIX `/demos/maryland-driveway-restore-wp/`
   or similar). This gives a real admin login (use the "Temporary Login Without
   Password" plugin for a magic link in the proposal) while obeying the
   tunnel-is-sacred rule. Risks: WP path/URL rewriting behind a sub-path bridge,
   Docker on Windows Surface, Bricks licensing. Treat as a bonus, not the
   critical path; the proposal can DESCRIBE the real WP/Bricks/Rank Math stack as
   the delivery plan while the static demo carries the live click-through.

Planner: pick #1 as the build target, list #2 as an explicit optional stretch
with a go/no-go gate. CEO: arbitrate if demo-builder wants to attempt #2.

## Plan of attack (pipeline shape)
intake → planner → CEO → researcher → demo-builder → deploy → deploy-test →
media-capture → proposal-writer → evaluator. (with-deploy + with-ceo layout: a
real lead-capture endpoint and a live-route gate both matter here.)

## Quality guidance per downstream step
- **intake:** Capture EVERY explicit requirement as a checklist item — the 8
  Phase-1 pages, the 9 SEO requirements, the 8 tech-stack tools, the 6 mobile-first
  items, the homepage blueprint sections, the QR `/free-estimate` landing page,
  the 6 "Questions for Developers" (these MUST be answered point-by-point in the
  cover letter), and the proposal requirements (fixed Phase-1 price, separate
  Phase-2 estimate, timeline, portfolio, references, post-launch support). Record
  the budget band ($850–$1,200, Rocket hosting included for first couple months)
  and the 1-week launch constraint.
- **researcher:** Pull real Maryland/Annapolis driveway-restoration + sealcoating
  competitor sites for visual conventions and the premium gap. Confirm the
  `construction-company-website` demo as the closest structural clone (multi-page
  static home-services site already in `public/demos/`). Gather concrete details
  of Michael's **fortherecordmn.com** SEO/GA work to cite as proof. Source
  before/after asphalt imagery (royalty-free or generated).
- **planner:** Define the bespoke design system NOW (charcoal #1a1d1a-ish, white,
  forest green, big serif/clean-sans pairing à la Restoration Hardware; generous
  whitespace; before/after photography hero). Do NOT use michaelwegter.com's
  palette. Map every brief requirement → a demo feature or a deck claim.
- **demo-builder:** Mobile-first. Sticky Call Now + Text a Photo. Real working
  estimate form (Flask blueprint persists submissions; seed nothing sensitive).
  Embed LocalBusiness/Service/FAQ/Review JSON-LD, unique title/meta per page,
  logical H1–H3, ALT text. Build the dedicated `/free-estimate` QR landing page.
  Lighthouse/Core-Web-Vitals conscious (lazy images, no bloat).
- **proposal-writer:** Answer all 6 developer questions explicitly. Give a fixed
  Phase-1 price inside $850–$1,200 with Rocket hosting noted, and a SEPARATE
  Phase-2 estimate framed as an ongoing multi-state partnership. Cite
  fortherecordmn.com for SEO + GA proof. Include the live demo link in both the
  cover letter and deck. Michael's voice; no em/en dashes.

## Hard constraints reminder
- No em/en dashes anywhere. Bespoke client design, never the portfolio look.
- GitHub handle `mwegter95`.
- NEVER touch `~/.cloudflared/config.yml`. No separate tunnel ingress.
- Demo lives at `public/demos/maryland-driveway-restore/`; card via `workSamples.js`.
- Registry fields needed: client="Maryland Driveway Restore", category="Productivity"
  (or "Creative"), date ISO, frameStyle, color = forest green (#2f5d3a-ish).

